"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkbytesofpurpose_blog=globalThis.webpackChunkbytesofpurpose_blog||[]).push([[72011],{29201:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"about-my-mindset","metadata":{"permalink":"/mindset/about-my-mindset","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/mindset/mindset/2026-06-25-about-my-mindset.mdx","source":"@site/mindset/2026-06-25-about-my-mindset.mdx","title":"\ud83e\udde0 About My Mindset","description":"The inputs I deliberately keep to shape how I think: the quotes that moved me, the affirmations I return to, and the principles I live by.","date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"mindset","permalink":"/mindset/tags/mindset"},{"inline":true,"label":"meta","permalink":"/mindset/tags/meta"},{"inline":true,"label":"legend","permalink":"/mindset/tags/legend"}],"readingTime":1.59,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"about-my-mindset","title":"\ud83e\udde0 About My Mindset","sidebar_label":"\ud83e\udde0 About","description":"The inputs I deliberately keep to shape how I think: the quotes that moved me, the affirmations I return to, and the principles I live by.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["mindset","meta","legend"],"date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"legend","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Quotes That Moved Me","permalink":"/mindset/quotes-that-moved-me"}},"content":"This is where I keep the inputs I have **deliberately chosen to let shape how I think**. Not ideas\\nthat merely occurred to me (those are [Thoughts](/thoughts)), but the ones I curated in and keep on\\npurpose: the quotes that moved me, the affirmations I return to, the principles I live by. Less a\\nrecord of what crossed my mind than a record of what I let define it. (The *questions* I ask have\\ngrown into their own collection: [Questions](/questions).)\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Mindset is what I curate, not what occurs to me\\n\\nA thought and a mindset post can start from the same material; the difference is **deliberate\\ncuration**:\\n\\n- *Noticing* a quote is a passing thought. *Keeping* it, returning to it, letting it move me, is\\n  Mindset.\\n- An *observation* that crossed my mind is a Thought. The one I *adopt as a rule I live by* is\\n  Mindset.\\n- A line of advice I heard once is a thought. The affirmation I repeat to myself on hard days is\\n  Mindset.\\n\\nA thought graduates INTO my mindset the moment I deliberately keep it to shape how I think (one of\\n[three ways a thought can graduate](/thoughts/about-my-thoughts): act on it \u2192 an Initiative, keep it\\n\u2192 Mindset, distill it \u2192 Craft).\\n\\n## The kinds of mindset\\n\\nEach post is one curated input, tagged with its KIND:\\n\\n<MindsetKindLegend />\\n\\n## The parts of the mindset\\n\\n- [Quotes That Moved Me](/mindset/quotes-that-moved-me): the curated set, each with a note on why.\\n- [Affirmations for the Inner Game](/mindset/affirmations-for-the-inner-game): the deck I flip\\n  through when I need the right words.\\n- [The Song of Life](/mindset/the-song-of-life): a meditation on purpose, living, and letting go.\\n\\nThe *questions* I ask live in their own collection now: see [Questions](/questions) (and the legend\\nbehind them, [What I Ask Myself](/handbook/what-i-ask-myself)).\\n\\nBrowse the posts below."},{"id":"quotes-that-moved-me","metadata":{"permalink":"/mindset/quotes-that-moved-me","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/mindset/mindset/2026-06-25-quotes-that-moved-me.mdx","source":"@site/mindset/2026-06-25-quotes-that-moved-me.mdx","title":"Quotes That Moved Me","description":"A curated set of quotes that landed on me and stuck, with my reflection on why each one moved me and how it shapes the way I think.","date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"mindset","permalink":"/mindset/tags/mindset"},{"inline":true,"label":"quotes","permalink":"/mindset/tags/quotes"}],"readingTime":2.06,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"quotes-that-moved-me","title":"Quotes That Moved Me","kind":"quote-set","sidebar_label":"Quotes","description":"A curated set of quotes that landed on me and stuck, with my reflection on why each one moved me and how it shapes the way I think.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["mindset","quotes"],"date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83e\udde0 About My Mindset","permalink":"/mindset/about-my-mindset"},"nextItem":{"title":"The Song of Life","permalink":"/mindset/the-song-of-life"}},"content":"A running, curated set of the lines that actually moved me: not clever quotes I collected to sound\\ndeep, but the few that rearranged something in how I think. Each one has a short note on why it\\nlanded. Read the section that matches where your head is, and take what resonates.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## On the work itself\\n\\n<SectionBanner why=\\"The lines I reach for when I am tempted to chase a breakthrough instead of keeping the systems that compound.\\" />\\n\\n<QuoteSet>\\n\\n<Quote source=\\"Will Durant\\" cite=\\"often attributed to Aristotle\\" video=\\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m6-qeutzoR8\\" reflection=\\"It reframed mastery as something I build in the small, unglamorous reps rather than chase in a single breakthrough. It is why I care more about the systems I keep than the bursts I manage.\\">\\nWe are what we <Focus>repeatedly do</Focus>. Excellence, then, is not an act, but a <Focus>habit</Focus>.\\n</Quote>\\n\\n<Quote source=\\"Marcus Aurelius\\" cite=\\"via Ryan Holiday\\" reflection=\\"The thing blocking me is usually the thing worth doing. When I notice resistance now I lean toward it instead of around it, because that friction tends to mark where the growth is.\\">\\nThe obstacle is the way.\\n</Quote>\\n\\n</QuoteSet>\\n\\n## On doing it with others\\n\\n<SectionBanner why=\\"A standing correction to my instinct to do everything myself.\\" />\\n\\n<QuoteSet>\\n\\n<Quote source=\\"African proverb\\" reflection=\\"A quiet correction to my instinct to do everything myself. The work I am proudest of was slower because it was shared, and it lasted because of it.\\">\\nIf you want to go fast, <Focus>go alone</Focus>. If you want to go far, <Focus>go together</Focus>.\\n</Quote>\\n\\n</QuoteSet>\\n\\n## On what compounds\\n\\n<SectionBanner why=\\"The chain I come back to when I want a reminder that small inputs upstream decide who I become downstream.\\" />\\n\\n<PosterQuote source=\\"Frank Outlaw\\" cite=\\"often misattributed to Lao Tzu; the line traces to a 1977 Frank Outlaw saying\\">\\n<Beat lead=\\"Watch your\\" big=\\"THOUGHTS\\" />\\n<Beat lead=\\"they become your\\" big=\\"WORDS\\" />\\n<Beat lead=\\"watch your words, they become your\\" big=\\"ACTIONS\\" />\\n<Beat lead=\\"watch your actions, they become your\\" big=\\"HABITS\\" />\\n<Beat lead=\\"watch your habits, they become your\\" big=\\"CHARACTER\\" />\\n<Beat lead=\\"watch your character, it becomes your\\" big=\\"DESTINY\\" />\\n</PosterQuote>\\n\\n## Related\\n\\nFor the raw deck I flip through when I need the right words in a hard moment, see\\n[Affirmations for the Inner Game](/mindset/affirmations-for-the-inner-game): hundreds of\\nfaith-based and motivational lines, grouped by theme."},{"id":"the-song-of-life","metadata":{"permalink":"/mindset/the-song-of-life","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/mindset/mindset/2020-03-23-the-song-of-life.md","source":"@site/mindset/2020-03-23-the-song-of-life.md","title":"The Song of Life","description":"A set of philosophical reflections on life, death, purpose, words, and the strange symmetry between programs and existence.","date":"2020-03-23T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"philosophy","permalink":"/mindset/tags/philosophy"},{"inline":true,"label":"mindset","permalink":"/mindset/tags/mindset"}],"readingTime":4.37,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"the-song-of-life","title":"The Song of Life","kind":"reflection","sidebar_label":"Song of Life","description":"A set of philosophical reflections on life, death, purpose, words, and the strange symmetry between programs and existence.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["philosophy","mindset"],"date":"2020-03-23T00:00:00.000Z","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Quotes That Moved Me","permalink":"/mindset/quotes-that-moved-me"},"nextItem":{"title":"Affirmations for the Inner Game","permalink":"/mindset/affirmations-for-the-inner-game"}},"content":"These are reflections I\'ve collected over years of philosophical wandering: about\\nwhat life is for, why death isn\'t to be feared, the mystical weight of words, and\\nthe odd symmetry between writing a program and living a life. They aren\'t arguments\\nso much as meditations. Read them slowly.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Life\'s purpose and meaning\\n\\nThe Prophet (SAAW) loved God. How beautiful life is when you return to the one you\\nlove. And while you are away from your love, you learn to do what makes them happy.\\nYou do what you want, not knowing that your lover is aware. But fret not: love is\\ntrue, and all is forgiven in Love.\\n\\nWhat kind of life are you living if, at the end, you don\'t know where you are\\ngoing? You don\'t know what will happen to you?\\n\\n## The song of life\\n\\nMusic is inherently playful. The point is not to reach the end of the song; it\'s\\nthe song itself. You *play* the piano. You don\'t *work* the piano.\\n\\nYour life is your art. What is your art as an artist?\\n\\nLife is a musical thing. We were supposed to sing and dance, not rush to reach the\\nend. It\'s like Hajj: a pilgrimage to reach God, but once you\'re there, you dance\\nwith God.\\n\\n## Living and loving\\n\\nI live to live. I live to love. To love what I do. To do what I love.\\n\\nI love. I live. One day I will leave you, with my love, and go to the One that\\ncreated you and me to love.\\n\\n## Death, the return\\n\\nWhy do you fear death? You are simply returning to whom you love. He did not create\\nyou in vain. He will take care of you when you part.\\n\\n## The recursion of life\\n\\nIn nature: cells and planets. In life: death is the base case. Success in life\\nstarts at realizing death. Start working towards your death. I don\'t want to die\\nregretfully; I want to live towards my death.\\n\\nGod recursively created us: the ability to perpetuate yourself through your\\ngenerations, in our cells, the planets, the universe. What is the folded value of\\nhumanity?\\n\\n## Understanding purpose\\n\\nTo understand our purpose, we must understand why we were created. What use does God\\nhave from us? None. God doesn\'t need us to do anything; God is not benefiting from\\nus. So it\'s in our best interest to emulate God, to learn about God, to reflect the\\ndivine purpose.\\n\\nHow can you love God if you don\'t know God?\\n\\n## The power of words\\n\\n*Motivation on demand. And God said \\"Be\\" and it was.*\\n\\nWe underestimate the power of words. Words are powerful. We think in words. We sell\\nin words. We speak in words. We pursue with words. We are surrounded by words since\\nbirth. We fall in love through words. We transfer emotions through words. And when\\nwe pass, we are remembered through words.\\n\\nWords can make the hairs on our backs stand. We start wars over words. We form\\nalliances through words. Words drive the world. They drive the way we think about\\nourselves. They affect how we feel. They can make our day or break our day. Whether\\nwe like it or not, words have mystical powers over us.\\n\\nThat\'s why it\'s so important to surround ourselves with positive words: words that\\nmotivate us, that influence us to become better people, that remind us to believe in\\nourselves, that help keep us determined, that remind us that we are blessed.\\n\\nMind came before matter. Words came before the matter. Everything is language.\\nEverything can be described with words. God taught Adam all the words.\\n\\nWords can teach you how to cook. Words can inspire you. Words govern technology.\\nWe think in words. Some words were never meant to be. Some things were never meant\\nto be said. Some words are captured deep inside. Words have the power to change;\\nwords have the power to hold. Words can capture your essence for everyone else to\\nsee. Words can capture your mind for everyone to enjoy.\\n\\n## Understanding programming\\n\\nOur lives begin with an event (birth) and end with an event (death). What lies\\nin-between these two milestones is a collection of choices. Similarly, programs\\nstart with an event (double-clicking an icon) and end with an event (closing the\\nprogram), and what lies in-between is a collection of choices.\\n\\nChoices are black and white. Do I play soccer, or not play soccer?\\n\\nWe looked at a fish; we built ships. We looked at birds; we built planes. We looked\\nat humans; we built computers. Computers are a masterful manifestation of choices.\\n\\n## Understanding problem solving\\n\\nIs problem solving breaking things down to the simplest pieces, then piecing them\\nback together in a structured fashion, by sequencing the elements and relating them?\\n\\nWe conquered chemistry through elements. We conquered computers through bits, through\\ndata. Language is letters and symbols. Language is assigning meaning to words.\\nLanguage is assigning meaning to the meaning of different sequences of words.\\n\\nIs problem solving breaking things down to the smallest *meaningful* elements, or\\nsimply breaking things down to the smallest *possible* element?\\n\\nDo letters have meaning by themselves? Do bits have meaning by themselves?"},{"id":"affirmations-for-the-inner-game","metadata":{"permalink":"/mindset/affirmations-for-the-inner-game","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/mindset/mindset/2019-01-01-affirmations-for-the-inner-game.md","source":"@site/mindset/2019-01-01-affirmations-for-the-inner-game.md","title":"Affirmations for the Inner Game","description":"A collection of faith-based and motivational affirmations I\'ve returned to over the years, organized by theme: faith, strength, discipline, failure, focus, confidence, and living fully.","date":"2019-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"mindset","permalink":"/mindset/tags/mindset"}],"readingTime":9.78,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"affirmations-for-the-inner-game","title":"Affirmations for the Inner Game","kind":"reflection","sidebar_label":"Inner Game","description":"A collection of faith-based and motivational affirmations I\'ve returned to over the years, organized by theme: faith, strength, discipline, failure, focus, confidence, and living fully.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["mindset"],"date":"2019-01-01T00:00:00.000Z","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"The Song of Life","permalink":"/mindset/the-song-of-life"}},"content":"For years I\'ve kept a running list of affirmations: faith-based reminders, lines from motivational talks, and one-liners that snapped me out of a rut. Some are scripture-adjacent, some are pure hype, some are questions I ask myself. They were scattered across notebooks and notes apps until I gathered and grouped them by theme.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nI\'m sharing them here the way I use them: not as a system to follow, but as a deck to flip through when you need the right words. Read the section that matches where your head is. Take what resonates, leave the rest.\\n\\n## Faith & Trusting God\\n\\n### Order my steps\\n- He is orchestrating your strength\\n- He is giving you steps you are capable of handling\\n- Hold his hand and start to climb to your potential\\n- Order my steps Lord\\n- I trust you\\n- You have equipped me with everything I need right now\\n- Your life will move in the direction of your words\\n- What better words than his\\n- The Names of God should drive your actions\\n- I put in him all it takes to withstand the pressure\\n- Walk by faith and not by sight\\n- God just needs to will to do, you need to act. Will is not enough!\\n\\n### God has a plan\\n- GOD HAS SOMETHING IN PLAN FOR YOU\\n- HE WON\'T GIVE YOU SOMETHING YOU CAN\'T TAKE\\n- HE WON\'T GIVE YOU A CHALLENGE YOU CAN\'T HANDLE\\n- HE IS BUILDING EVERYONE OF US\\n- God is not preparing the blessing for you, God is preparing you for the blessings!\\n- Any time you get anything too soon, you will trip on the steps!\\n- What is God preparing you for?\\n\\n### God is with you\\n- GOD HAS ALWAYS BEEN THERE AND HE ALWAYS WILL\\n- YOU DON\'T HAVE TO SEE HIM TO KNOW THAT SOMEONE IS LOOKING OUT FOR YOU\\n- God knows that you will be able to bear the burden he gave you, and that you will come out of it stronger, better!\\n- God will not present you with something you can\'t handle!\\n- Have you been trusted with some trouble?!\\n- YOU NEVER PROMISE THE OBVIOUS, YOU ONLY PROMISE WHEN THERE IS A CAUSE FOR DOUBT. GOD PROMISES THAT HE WONT GIVE YOU SOMETHING YOU CAN HANDLE!\\n\\n### Pray to Him\\n- DO NOT ABUSE GOD\'S MERCY!\\n- THE PRESENCE OF A STORM DOES NOT INDICATE THE ABSENCE OF GOD\\n- Why do you only beg Him when it starts to storm?!\\n\\n### Faith as a force\\n- Faith is the oil that takes the friction out of living\\n- It all starts with belief\\n- BELIEVE!\\n- Faith finds a way!\\n- I am going to show you how great I am! ~ Muhammad Ali\\n- I work on making the people around me believe that we are going to be great.\\n- Don\'t believe its a lack of funds that makes you unsuccessful, its a lack of belief!\\n- HE IS ABLE WHO THINKS HE IS ABLE\\n- I WILL\\n- Change your garments!\\n- Prepare for something that hasn\'t happened yet!\\n\\n## Strength, Pain & Endurance\\n\\n### Let hardships build you\\n- Things don\'t happen by accident! I didn\'t stumble upon you by accident!\\n- The steps of a good man are ordered by God!\\n- Experiences build you. They give you faith.\\n- Be thankful for experiences\\n- Be thankful for goodbyes\\n- When pain comes it\'s time to show your character\\n- I never fail, I only have learning experiences!\\n- NOTHING JUST HAPPENS!\\n- Praise God in the middle of the pain, trust where He is taking you!\\n- Your strength is perfected in the weak places of life!\\n- I want you to praise me in the middle of the pain then I know you trust me that I am taking you somewhere!\\n- Im sickening to talking to people who think that things just happen.\\n\\n### Deal with pain\\n- It\'s how you handle the pain!\\n- I CHOOSE TO FIGHT BACK!\\n- PAIN IS NOT PERMANENT!\\n- PAIN IS TEMPORARY!\\n- I can guarantee you, if you work through your pain, on the other side, there is a reward!\\n- I\'M HAVING A CHARACTER BUILDING DAY!\\n\\n### Learn from pain\\n- Our Pains Are Similar, Our Solutions Are Different!\\n- Somebody can take the hand you\'ve been dealt and be successful!\\n- What Can I Do With The Stuff You Gave Me!\\n\\n### Be strong\\n- Be strong! And have the audacity to keep being strong!\\n- When you are strong, nobody can shake you\\n- She was strong enough to push through\\n- If you bend you won\'t break\\n- I was weak, I was vulnerable, I was hurting, I was in pain, I was at my worst, but I was still a giant!\\n- I\'M A GIANT! I\'M A FREAK! WHEN I WANTED TO FOLD I DIDN\'T FOLD!\\n- YOU CAN\'T MESS WITH A HURT GIANT!\\n- YOUR PAIN WON\'T STOP ME! IF YOU WANT ME TO STOP, YOU HAVE TO KILL ME!\\n\\n### Never quit\\n- THE UNSTOPPABLE MARCH\\n- DON\'T STOP TILL YOU REACH THE TOP!\\n- IF YOU ARE WEAK YOU WILL QUIT!\\n- YOU CANT AFFORD TO BE TIRED!\\n- TOUGH TIMES DONT LAST FOREVER!\\n- TOUGH TIMES DON\'T LAST, TOUGH PEOPLE DO!\\n- You cannot be a WAIVER!\\n- Be relentless\\n- IF YOU GET TIRED, LEARN TO REST, NOT QUIT!\\n- When You Cannot, You Must!\\n- IF YOU QUIT THIS TIME, YOU WILL QUIT AGAIN!\\n- Quitters never win! Winners never quit!\\n- They were ready to quit, but they didn\'t. Don\'t be a quitter!\\n- Go where people believe you are unstoppable!\\n\\n## Discipline, Action & Drive\\n\\n### Act now\\n- This Moment. This Moment. Now. Now. Now. Do You Get What I Am Saying!\\n- You need to work out the muscle of doing!\\n- Push forward and take action anyway!\\n- Take consistent action everyday!\\n- If I don\'t do this work, ... who will!\\n- One Good Deed Leads To Another!\\n- You Cant Live At All Unless You Live Fully Now. START!\\n- ACTIONS EXPRESS PRIORITIES!\\n- You have just got to make one more decision!\\n- Ideation without execution is delusion!\\n- Thinking is the first step towards a revolution!\\n\\n### Discipline yourself\\n- Discipline Yourself!\\n- Your life will never change if you do not do the things you do not feel like doing!\\n- What are your MUSTs?!\\n- We don\'t get what we want, we get what we have to have!\\n- What changes people is when their should\'s become musts!\\n- What must you do?!\\n\\n### Drive and passion\\n- What drives you?!\\n- Let Love Drive You!\\n- Empires Fall... Love Survives!\\n- The Real Revolution, The Revolution Of The Mind, The Loveolution\\n- Purpose is your belief in motion!\\n- DON\'T PURSUE PROCESS. PURSUE PURPOSE!\\n- PASSIONS AND PURPOSE ALWAYS PRODUCE PROFIT!\\n- Its about history ... that never repeats itself!\\n- Let your passion take you places!\\n\\n### Be thankful\\n- Trade what upsets you - the expectations that are not being met - with appreciation for what you have!\\n\\n## Risk, Failure & Imperfection\\n\\n### Be ready to fail\\n- ADOPT A FAIL FIRST MENTALITY!\\n- DO YOU HAVE THE GUTS TO FAIL?\\n- IF YOU DON\'T FAIL ... YOU ARE NOT TRYING!\\n\\n### Avoid perfection\\n- If you have everything under control, you are moving too slow!\\n- ENGINEERS ARE TOO OBSESSED WITH PERFECTION TO DO ANYTHING!\\n- THERE ARE STAGES TO A PRODUCT ...\\n- YOU DON\'T INVEST IN PERFECTING YOUR TECH UNTIL YOU ARE CONFIDENT IN YOUR TECH!\\n\\n## Focus & Self-Mastery\\n\\n### Be focused\\n- You can\'t afford to be a wandering generality!\\n- You must be a meaningful specific!\\n- You have to really be committed to something to get everything you can out of it!\\n- You can\'t do everything at once...\\n\\n### Focus on your strengths\\n- Are you doing things right or are you doing the right things?\\n- Turn your strengths into superpowers ...\\n\\n### Be resourceful\\n- How resourceful are you?\\n- What resources do you have?\\n\\n### Be mindful of your thoughts\\n- What thoughts do you allow into your mind?!\\n- Pay attention to your inner dialog\\n\\n### Be mindful of your tongue\\n- Words are powerful!\\n\\n### Listen closely\\n- Listen to your intuition, the voice that tells you this is what you could do!\\n\\n## Confidence & Fearlessness\\n\\n### Confidence through experience\\n- You have been through plenty!\\n- You have seen enough!\\n- EGO is the anesthesia that deadens the pain of stupidity\\n- Pride is the burden of a foolish person\\n\\n### Self-belief\\n- Trust your ideas\\n- You are lead!\\n- Promote yourself\\n\\n### Accepting praise\\n- Humiliating yourself is not humble\\n\\n### Be fearless\\n- Fear finds you in different ways.\\n- The Illusion of Security Robs Ambition!\\n- You don\'t want to be secure, you want to be strong\\n\\n### Stand your ground\\n- WALK ALONE IF YOU HAVE TO!\\n- Don\'t be mad at people who stop clapping\\n- At some point in your life you will find yourself alone\\n- Stand Your Ground\\n\\n## Identity, Purpose & Living Fully\\n\\n### Mindset reminders\\n- It\'s important to sort through the things I want... as they partially capture WHY I DO what I do!\\n- We don\'t complain on the things we can\'t change!\\n- When will you stop eating dirt\\n- Stop complaining about where you are!\\n\\n### Be unique\\n- THEIR CAN ONLY BE 1, AND YOU ARE IT!!\\n- DONT LET THE WORLD TELL YOU WHO YOU ARE\\n- You are different because of God! Because you need to do something for his name!\\n- The fact that you are different is not an accident!\\n- Everything that you are is for a reason!\\n- You are the sum of all of your experiences, thoughts and skills\\n- OWN YOUR STORY\\n- DONT LET THE WORLD TELL YOU WHAT TO REGRET\\n- If you don\'t like where you are from, you can never love where you are going\\n- YOU DESERVE TO BE AROUND PEOPLE THAT PUSH YOU!\\n\\n### Life is temporary\\n- What dreams will die with you?\\n- What talents will die with you?\\n- How you living?\\n- We either live our dreams or live our fears, which one are you living?\\n- ALL HUMANS DIE BUT FEW HAVE LIVED!\\n- LIFE IS EITHER A DARING ADVENTURE ... OR NOTHING!\\n\\n### Unleash yourself\\n- I CAN, I WILL, I MUST!\\n- Free Yourself From The Shackles Of Your Mind!\\n- A lot of people like to complain but they wont do anything about their situation.\\n- YOU could have been free years ago!\\n- The Real Battle Ground Is In Your Mind!\\n- A New Outfit Doesn\'t Make New You A New Person!\\n- A New Life Comes From A New Mind And A New Way Of Looking At Your Life\\n- Its What You Say About You THAT Threatens Your Destiny!\\n- YOU HAVE TO FIX THE MIND BEFORE YOU CAN ACCEPT A BLESSING!\\n- If you don\'t change your attitude, you wont reach your altitude!\\n- Exercise your mind!\\n- Rethink your mountaintop!\\n- I am going to do everything in my power to become a victor not a victim!\\n\\n### You matter\\n- You must realize who you are!\\n- Decide you love your self enough!\\n- Repeat after me: I am good enough!\\n- We\'re So Busy Studying Other People We Fail To Study Ourselves\\n- Do not Allow The Opinion Of Others To Control Your Future\\n- You can\'t relive my experience!\\n- You can\'t imitate my passion!\\n- You can\'t replicate my will!\\n- You can\'t live my vision!\\n- You get in life what you deserve not what you want!\\n- Treat Your Voice Like A Kite And The Wind Is The Song. - Pharrell Williams\\n- Use your genius on your own behalf\\n- Act on your own behalf!\\n- Act on your dreams!\\n- Turn your life into a work of art because anything less is a tragedy!\\n- I haven\'t had my most creative moment yet!\\n- DEEP DOWN IN YOUR HEART YOU KNOW YOU ARE NOT LIVING TO YOUR TRUE POTENTIAL!\\n- What will you do before your body perishes?\\n\\n### Wisdom and notes\\n- Judge a tree by the fruit that it bears!\\n- When you\'re poor, you have to dig inside for value!\\n- The toughest battles come to the toughest warriors!\\n- I am more than my mind! I have a heart and soul!\\n- As I mature my thinking ... different quotes take on different meanings ...\\n\\n## A note on these\\n\\nThese aren\'t original to me. They\'re collected over years from sermons, speeches, books, and the occasional 2 a.m. realization, then filed under the themes above. The point of keeping them isn\'t to memorize a creed. It\'s to have the right sentence within reach when the moment calls for it."}]}}')}}]);